coolmat.com/kr shows Korean version
coolmat.com shows English version

Polylang lets us create 

In header.php where the KR | EN hard coding is. 

Put in anchor tag that is:

<a lang="ko-KR" hreflang="ko-KR" href='<?php echo site_url('/kr'); ?>">KR</a> | <a lang="en-GB" hreflang="en-GB" href='<?php echo site_url(); ?>">EN</a> 

3 attributes
lang and hreflang - used by browsers to detect when languages are supported
href - gives us website URL and puts a /kr on the end and if we don't put anything into the brackets, it gives us the english version. 